Package: create-repo-auto
Version: 1.2.33
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash, curl, git
Maintainer: Your Name <you@example.com>
Description: Easily create and auto-sync Git repositories across GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket.
 create-repo-auto is a CLI tool that helps developers create, push, and continuously sync Git repositories with GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket — all from the terminal.
 .
 ✨ Features include:
  - Automatic Git initialization and remote setup
  - Support for GitHub, GitLab, and Bitbucket
  - Interactive first-time setup (with config file)
  - Auto-sync with cron (Linux/WSL) or launchd (macOS)
  - Self-update support
  - Detailed logs and error handling
  - Supports public and private repositories, with GitHub teams
